name: WestJet's IMPRESSIVE Premium Offering - 737-600 Calgary to Abbotsford
description:
On their 737 family, WestJet has a small Premium cabin up front, with three rows of 2x2 seating, formerly known as WestJet “Plus”.

Anyone booking a Premium or Business Class fare with WestJet to Europe on a connecting itinerary, also receives a seat in Premium on board the shorter flight. While Premium on the Q400s and Saab 340s isn’t all that different from regular economy, the 737s are a different story!

Having flown their Dreamliner in Business long haul, I booked Premium on this one hour flight from Calgary to Abbotsford to see what they have to offer up front on a domestic 737 flight.
